        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 19 at 7:32PM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 732 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms over Roaring River, or near Ronda, moving east at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Jonesville...
Ronda...
Windy Gap...
Hays...
Pleasant Hill...
Wilkes County Airport...
and Clingman.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
